CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1958, pg. 5 reads: "Hosts - Grand Inspector General of St. Cyprian Consistory 4, host lodge are, seated, left to right: W.T.Poole, Sovereign Inspector General; S.A. Jennings, 33 degree, and, standing: 33 degree Masons W.B.Richardson, J.W. Givens, M.L. Dempsey, J.E. Green, W.R. Webster, J.W.Bryant, W.C. Douglas and R.V. Miller of Clairton."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of ten 33 degree Masons, seated from left: W.T.Poole, and S.A. Jennings; standing from left: W.B.Richardson, J.W. Givens, M.L. Dempsey, J.E. Green, W.R. Webster, J.W.Bryant, W.C. Douglas, and R.V. Miller, gathered around small sofa in Fort Pitt Hotel for the 75th Annual Session of the United Supreme Council of 33-Degree Masons
